\begin_layout Standard
The therapist selects 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Marco-Polo Game
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Goal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal of the game is to help the child to recognize spatial relations
 with Teo.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Rules
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The child and Teo share sufficiently large space to move around.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The game starts with a ’blindfolded’ Teo, which explains the child the dynamic
 of the game.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Teo prompts the kid to move away from him.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Anytime Teo needs help would ask ’Where are you, (name of the child)?’ and
 the child must answer back ’Teo, here!’.
\end_layout

